23/08/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer praised the progress achieved by Albania thus far, while urging the country to move ahead with reforms which will eventually result in NATO membership. 
In a letter to Parliament Speaker Jozefina Topalli and Foreign Minister Besnik Mustafaj -- quoted by local media Wednesday (23 August) -- de Hoop Scheffer stressed the importance of strengthening Albanian institutions. 
He also emphasised the positive role Tirana plays in the region, especially as regards the Kosovo situation. 
(Albanian News, MRT - 23/08/06)
